Movement and Tactical Behavior: Historically, Soviet units maneuvered in tightly controlled echelons with predetermined battle drills. Modern Russian BTGs, by contrast, exhibit more adaptive maneuver tactics learned from recent conflicts. For instance, studies comparing Russian operations in Ukraine to Soviet-era warfare note that Russian BTGs operate with a mission-command approach, delegating initiative to battalion commanders in the fieldâ€‹
